### 1. Install mise (Tool Version Manager)
```bash
curl https://mise.run | bash
```
Follow the prompt to add it to your shell profile (e.g. `~/.zshrc` or `~/.bashrc`).

### 2. Clone This Template Repo (Optional)
You can explore this template locally, but **do not modify `copier.yaml`**.
Instead, use it to generate a new service project.

### 3. Scaffold a New FastAPI Microservice
```bash
copier copy gh:your-org/fastapi-service-template my-new-service
cd my-new-service
```
Copier will prompt you for:
- Project name
- Python version
- Description

### 4. Install All Required Tools
```bash
mise install
```
This installs the exact versions of Python, Poetry, Copier, and Pre-commit.

### 5. Install Dependencies and Enable Git Hooks
```bash
poetry install
pre-commit install
```

### 6. Start the Application
```bash
docker-compose up
```
Visit: [http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000)

### 7. Run Tests
```bash
pytest
```

### 8. Push to GitHub
```bash
git init
git remote add origin git@github.com:your-org/my-new-service.git
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git push -u origin main
```

### 9. Update from Template Later
When the base template improves:
```bash
copier update
```
It will re-apply updates and let you choose what to overwrite.
